Quarterly commentary  



Total returns details  






People and process

Firms
Wellington Management Company LLP
Product management
Vanguard GNMA Fund seeks a moderate and sustainable level of current income by investing at least 80% of its assets in Government National Mortgage Association (GNMA) pass-through certificates, which are fixed income securities representing part ownership in a pool of mortgage loans backed by the U.S. government. The investment advisor, Wellington Management Company LLP, seeks to maintain a high yield and predictable income stream by selecting securities with strong relative value among the broad range of available securities, and by appropriately positioning the fund in changing economic environments.
